Rural Development and Land Reform Minister Gugile Nkwinti officially handed over part of a 904-hectare farm near Komani to 102 of its residents on Friday. The Gallawater Farm beneficiaries are part of a “one household, one hectare” and “one household, five sheep” government programme which envisages that as a household’s small flock grows, so does their land allocation. According to the department’s Malerato Molokoane, it is part of a strategy to combat poverty by creating sustainable employment in rural households by rekindling a class of black smallholder farmers. “For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions”.   The Democratic Alliance is to ask public protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane to investigate the Land Reform Minister over the R97-million sale of a farm to a friend. The Sunday Times reported yesterday that Minister Gugile Nkwinti had introduced a Luthuli House comrade “shopping” for a thriving Limpopo farm to one of… February 13, 2017 In "Featured" The Birbury farmworkers in the Bathurst pineapple belt, between Grahamstown and Port Alfred, are on the cusp of having their poverty-stricken lives changed for the better now that the rural development department has rolled out its co-ownership land redistribution policy on the farm they have for than 40 years been… August 29, 2017 In "Opinion" Rural Development and Land Reform Minister Gugile Nkwinti yesterday chose the funeral of his one-time attorney and close friend Judge Bonisile Sandi to dismiss allegations that he was involved in dirty dealings in land. For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for… March 11, 2017 In "Featured"